Privacy Policy for Out of the Loop
Last Updated:
26 November, 2024
Thank you for playing
Out of the Loop
! Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to being transparent about how your information is handled. This privacy policy explains what data may be collected when you use the game, how it is used, and your rights.
What Data We Collect
Out of the Loop
does not include any online components and does not actively collect, store, or process any personal or gameplay data.
However, the game is built using the Unity game engine, which may collect certain information by default. This data collection is managed by Unity Technologies and is subject to their privacy practices. Unity may collect:
Device information (e.g., hardware model, operating system version).
IP address.
Game crash reports and performance data.
Unity uses this data to improve its services and ensure the game runs smoothly.
How Your Data Is Used
As the developers of
Out of the Loop
, we do not access, use, or store any of the data collected by Unity. Any data collected is managed exclusively by Unity and used for purposes such as analytics, debugging, and game performance optimization.
For more information on Unityâ€™s data collection practices and how to opt out, please visit their privacy policy:
Unity Privacy Policy and Data Opt-Out Options
.
Third-Party Services
Other than Unity, no third-party services are integrated into
Out of the Loop
. The game does not include advertisements, online multiplayer, or other features that would require additional data collection.
Your Privacy Rights
Since
Out of the Loop
does not collect any user data directly, there is no data for us to modify, share, or delete. If you wish to manage or restrict the data collected by Unity, please refer to their privacy settings and opt-out options in their policy linked above.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about this privacy policy or your data, feel free to contact us at:
Email:
tastyrook@tastyrook.com
By playing
Out of the Loop
, you agree to the terms outlined in this privacy policy. We recommend reviewing Unity's privacy policy for further details on how your data is handled by their services.
Thank you for playing
Out of the Loop
!
